Author: Jason Harvey <jason@deepadata.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 12 11:42:10 2026 +1000

    fix(schemas): accept explicit null on nullable enum fields (conformance fix, v0.8.1 errata candidate)
    
    Implementation-conformance fix, NOT a spec change. The EDM whitepaper
    section 5.2 (Population Invariants: No Omission, No Inference) REQUIRES
    every field to be present with an explicit null when unsupported by the
    input - and the extraction prompts say "pick ONE or null". But 24 enum
    fields in the reference JSON schemas declared type ["string","null"]
    while omitting null from the adjacent enum list, which JSON Schema
    evaluates independently of type. The schemas were rejecting exactly what
    the spec text mandates: seal() failed on every low-signal artifact whose
    extraction correctly returned null (23/60 in the 2026-06-10
    archive-sample run; 20 of those now validate, remaining 3 are separate
    extraction-output defects).
    
    Fields corrected (24):
    - constellation: temporal_context, memory_type, media_format,
      narrative_archetype, relational_perspective, temporal_rhythm
    - gravity: emotional_density, valence, viscosity, temporal_decay,
      adaptation_trajectory
    - impulse: drive_state, motivational_orientation, temporal_focus,
      directionality, social_visibility, urgency, risk_posture, agency_level,
      regulation_state, attachment_style
    - milky_way: visibility_context
    - edm.v0.8.extended.schema.json (inlined gravity): valence,
      recurrence_pattern
    
    Upstream: flag for edm-spec v0.8.1 changelog/errata - "reference schemas
    corrected to accept explicit null per section 5.2". No field semantics
    change; v0.8.0 artifacts are unaffected except that spec-conformant ones
    now validate.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

